{
  "stem": "293.3",
  "chunk_idx": 15,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Till, one day, maybe four or five days later, he said, I just found out that they are in Auschwitz, and I will try everything to get them out.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He sent a beautiful German woman with lots of gifts and lots of money to-- to the Officer Hess, you know, the SS officer in charge, to talk with him.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Some things happened between him and her, and-- and they gives and the sausages and liquor and vodka what Schindler sended to him with a note that he will be coming himself to pick up the women.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he came.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I don't know the women knew that he was there, but we knew that he went there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And few days later, he came in, the women are coming.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And six o'clock in November, beginning of November, the gate open of the factory, six o'clock and it was foggy day, you know?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We stay on the balcony because the place-- our barracks were upstairs, and the factory was downstairs in the building, the front building.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the factory was a tremendous factory-- and-- like a shadow, you know, in the fog, the women were coming.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I couldn't recognize my wife, but she said to me later on that she saw me over there on the balcony.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then they came in.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They got hot food, and I builded-- because I was again welder-- I could go anyplace I wanted.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I start to bring-- there were window to the latrine, but you couldn't open the window to the latrine because it was against the law.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the latrine was for the women, and the other latrine was for men.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
